Before to start installation on worker node please ensure all these ports are allowed 
https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/networking/ports-and-protocols/


KUBERNETES_VERSION=v1.32
CRIO_VERSION=v1.32
swapoff -a
modprobe br_netfilter
sysctl -w net.ipv4.ip_forward=1

curl -fsSL https://pkgs.k8s.io/core:/stable:/$KUBERNETES_VERSION/deb/Release.key |
    gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes-apt-keyring.gpg

echo "deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes-apt-keyring.gpg] https://pkgs.k8s.io/core:/stable:/$KUBERNETES_VERSION/deb/ /" |
    tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/kubernetes.list

curl -fsSL https://download.opensuse.org/repositories/isv:/cri-o:/stable:/$CRIO_VERSION/deb/Release.key |
    gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/cri-o-apt-keyring.gpg

echo "deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/cri-o-apt-keyring.gpg] https://download.opensuse.org/repositories/isv:/cri-o:/stable:/$CRIO_VERSION/deb/ /" |
    tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/cri-o.list

apt update -y
apt install kubelet cri-o -y

systemctl start crio
systemctl start kubelet
systemctl enable crio
systemctl enable kubelet

------------------------------
Now to join API Master server from worker node  the below information is required

API Server IP | Port
API Token  (It is required one time only when you join the master cluster )      # kubeadm token list  -- run command on master node
# kubeadm token delete <token>
# kubeadm token create --ttl-duration=0
# kubeadm token create

Certificate  (It is required to communication trust relationship, These certs provised from master node)   # ls /etc/kubernetes/pki -- on master node ca.crt 

To Join cluster command :--
# kubeadm token create --print-join-command

-------------------------------------------------------
Additional Network configuration:

L-3:

1. Flannel
2. Weave
3. Ovn-kubernetes
4. OVS
5. Calico : recommended

Installtion : https://docs.tigera.io/calico/latest/getting-started/kubernetes/self-managed-onprem/onpremises
download the manifest : curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/projectcalico/calico/v3.30.2/manifests/calico.yaml -O

kubectl create -f calico.yaml    ## Run this command to configure the network
kubectl get ippool -o yaml       ##  To check which IP Pool has been configured




